--- Comment #12 from Thomas Blume <thomas.blume@suse.com> ---
(In reply to Philippe Condé from comment #11)
> Questions
> 
> 1.Can I delete the first line in /etc/dracut.conf.d/05-convertfs.conf?

yes, this line is obsolete.

> 2.Can I delete the rd.convertfs in grub bootloader via Yast?

yes, you can delete this too.

> 3. When do we need a rd.convertfs in the bootloader command line and what is
> it doing?

This is to convert the obsolete directory /var/run into a symlink, like it is
on new installations.
When /var/run stays a directory, you will have the content of this directory
twice, one time below /var/run and one time below /run.
It seems that on your machine, the conversion of /var/run to a symlink fails
for any reason.
That makes the conversion code adding the conversion parameters again at each
package update.
I'm working on a fix for this and will provide a testpackage when it is ready.

-- 
